  <Docs>
    <summary>Represents a four-byte OpenType/TrueType tag value used to identify font tables, variation axes, and other named entities.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFourByteTag` wraps a 32-bit unsigned integer that encodes four ASCII characters packed
in big-endian order: the first character occupies bits 31–24 and the last occupies bits 7–0.
This matches the standard OpenType four-character code (4CC) format.

Create a tag from a string with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKFourByteTag.Parse(System.String)>, from
individual characters with the four-character constructor, or implicitly from a raw `uint`.

`SKFourByteTag` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Parse from string (padded with spaces if shorter than 4 characters)
var weightAxis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght");
var nameTable  = SKFourByteTag.Parse("name");

// Construct from characters directly
var os2Table = new SKFourByteTag('O', 'S', '/', '2');

Console.WriteLine(weightAxis.ToString()); // "wght"
```
]]></format></remarks>
